- **Describe** incremental backups: saving only the data that has changed since the last backup <marks>A1</marks>, which allows for frequent recovery points and efficient use of storage <marks>A1</marks>;
- **Describe** disk mirroring: maintaining an exact, real-time copy of the database on another server or disk <marks>A1</marks>, allowing for immediate failover and recovery if the primary system fails <marks>A1</marks>;

